  "response_text": "Creating a balanced diet plan for weight loss involves incorporating a variety of foods that provide essential nutrients while also creating a calorie deficit. Here's a sample 7-day meal plan that emphasizes whole foods, lean proteins, healthy fats, and plenty of fruits and vegetables. Adjust portion sizes based on your individual caloric needs, and consult with a healthcare provider or nutritionist before making significant changes to your diet.\n\n### Sample 7-Day Balanced Diet Plan for Weight Loss\n\n#### Day 1\n- **Breakfast:** Oatmeal topped with fresh berries and a tablespoon of almond butter\n- **Snack:** A small apple with a handful of walnuts\n- **Lunch:** Grilled chicken salad with mixed greens, cherry tomatoes, cucumbers, and balsamic vinaigrette\n- **Snack:** Greek yogurt with a sprinkle of cinnamon\n- **Dinner:** Baked salmon with quinoa and steamed broccoli\n\n#### Day 2\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie with spinach, banana, protein powder, and almond milk\n- **Snack:** Carrot sticks with hummus\n- **Lunch:** Turkey and avocado wrap in a whole wheat tortilla with lettuce and tomato\n- **Snack:** A pear\n- **Dinner:** Stir-fried tofu with mixed vegetables and brown rice\n\n#### Day 3\n- **Breakfast:** Scrambled eggs with spinach and whole-grain toast\n- **Snack:** Cucumber slices with guacamole\n- **Lunch:** Lentil soup with a side salad (mixed greens, bell peppers, lemon vinaigrette)\n- **Snack:** Cottage cheese with pineapple\n- **Dinner:** Grilled shrimp tacos with cabbage slaw on corn tortillas\n\n#### Day 4\n- **Breakfast:** Chia pudding made with almond milk, topped with sliced kiwi and a sprinkle of nuts\n- **Snack:** A small orange\n- **Lunch:** Quinoa salad with black beans, corn, diced bell peppers, and lime dressing\n- **Snack:** Celery sticks with peanut butter\n- **Dinner:** Baked chicken breast with sweet potato and green beans\n\n#### Day 5\n- **Breakfast:** Greek yogurt parfait with granola and mixed berries\n- **Snack:** A banana\n- **Lunch:** Spinach and feta stuffed portobello mushrooms with a side of mixed greens\n- **Snack:** A handful of almonds\n- **Dinner:** Beef stir-fry with broccoli, bell peppers, and brown rice\n\n#### Day 6\n- **Breakfast:** Smoothie bowl topped with sliced bananas, chia seeds, and a few granola clusters\n- **Snack:** A hard-boiled egg\n- **Lunch:** Chickpea salad with diced cucumbers, tomatoes, red onion, and a lemon-tahini dressing\n- **Snack:** Sliced bell peppers with tzatziki sauce\n- **Dinner:** Zucchini noodles with marinara sauce and turkey meatballs\n\n#### Day 7\n- **Breakfast:** Whole grain pancakes topped with sliced strawberries and a drizzle of honey\n- **Snack:** A small handful of mixed nuts\n- **Lunch:** Grilled vegetable and quinoa bowl with a lemon dressing\n- **Snack:** A cup of mixed berries\n- **Dinner:** Baked tilapia with asparagus and a side of wild rice\n\n### Additional Tips\n- **Hydration:** Drink plenty of water throughout the day. Aim for at least 8 cups (64 ounces) and more if you're active.\n- **Portion Control:** Be mindful of portion sizes to maintain a calorie deficit for weight loss.\n- **Physical Activity:** Incorporate regular exercise, such as walking, running, cycling, or strength training, to enhance weight loss.\n- **Meal Prep:** Preparing meals in advance can help you stick to your plan and avoid unhealthy choices.\n\nThis meal plan is meant to serve as a guide. Feel free to mix and match meals and snacks based on your preferences and dietary restrictions.",
